Government is still assessing the cost of the damage caused by the KwaZulu-Natal floods. The UNDP in South Africa has reallocated R21m of its budget to flood relief. Ayodele Odusola speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The UN will monitor how funds it's donated to KwaZulu-Natal flood relief will be spent. The body is providing R21-million to help victims of the natural disaster. It says it will work with NGOs and communities themselves.